The paper deals with the computation of regular expression derivatives, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also presents a theoretical framework for this computation, which involves the use of generic structures and the construction of automata, both of which are topics in mathematical logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the finiteness of sets of derivatives, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and theorems and proofs (cs.THEORY).
